This paper discusses the use of genetic algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning and optimization, to solve the Traveling Salesman Problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the specific characteristics of various crossover operators, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also presents experimental results, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the Traveling Salesman Problem is a classic problem in the field of robotics, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics).
